<section class="page-hero narrow">
  <p class="eyebrow">Buyer Verification Checklist</p>
  <h1>How buyers should verify a used wall printer.</h1>
  <p>Wall Printer Exchange is not an inspection, escrow, payment, shipping, or warranty provider. Use this checklist before any purchase decision.</p>
</section>
<section class="content-card checklist">
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Confirm the seller’s identity.</strong> Request the seller’s full name, company name, phone, email, business registration if applicable, and proof that they are authorized to sell the machine.</li>
    <li><strong>Confirm machine ownership.</strong> Ask for original invoice, purchase record, serial number, machine nameplate, and documents showing legal ownership or authorization.</li>
    <li><strong>Request recent photos and videos.</strong> Ask for clear recent photos of the full machine, printheads, ink system, control box, rails, accessories, software screen, and nameplate.</li>
    <li><strong>Arrange a live video demonstration.</strong> Ask the seller to show startup, movement, printing, and a real wall print or test print during a live call.</li>
    <li><strong>Check printhead condition.</strong> Request nozzle test results, printhead model, print quality evidence, ink flow status, and any replaced, blocked, or damaged printheads.</li>
    <li><strong>Check included accessories.</strong> Confirm rails, extension poles, computer, software, dongle, ink, spare parts, power cables, packaging materials, manuals, and tools.</li>
    <li><strong>Confirm machine history.</strong> Ask about production year, purchase year, usage frequency, maintenance history, storage condition, repairs, known defects, and current working condition.</li>
    <li><strong>Arrange inspection when possible.</strong> For high-value or overseas machines, consider in-person inspection, third-party inspection, or local representative inspection before payment.</li>
    <li><strong>Confirm shipping and export details.</strong> Clarify packaging, pickup address, dimensions, weight, export documents, customs responsibilities, import duties, taxes, insurance, and shipping damage responsibility.</li>
    <li><strong>Use a written agreement.</strong> Confirm machine condition, included items, price, payment terms, delivery terms, inspection rights, refund terms, and after-sale responsibilities in writing.</li>
    <li><strong>Avoid risky payments.</strong> Do not send full payment before verifying seller identity, machine condition, and transaction terms. Wall Printer Exchange does not hold funds.</li>
  </ol>
</section>
